snippet.textDisplay:
Apparently, due to the apes and monkeys, the 'right' way to open up a banana is from the opposite end towards the stem - and the benefit of it is that all those filaments, that occasionally stick to the banana when you open it from the side of the stem, will get off with the peeling. I can confirm it works, significantly less filaments left on the banana if any. But on the flip side it's fricking hard to open it that way without a knife or an apes teeth... :-P

The orange fruits certainly weren't oranges, would agree with your tangerine theory there, though.

A very happy and healthy new year to you and Mrs. Beard.
